[8] Queensland
Date: Sat 1 Dec 2018
Source: The Mercury [edited]
https://www.themercury.com.au/news/breaking-news/whooping-cough-outbreak-in-qld-school/news-story/2c4dd0fbeae3990c58a8a55abab44fd6


An outbreak of whooping cough has forced a school on the Queensland/New South Wales border to close for the rest of the academic year.

St Mary's Catholic School in Goondiwindi has reported a number of students suffering from the highly contagious respiratory infection.

A Queensland Department of Education spokesperson says no state schools have experienced the level of infection at St Mary's, but they are monitoring the situation.

[Byline: Natalie Bochenski]

